The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and it has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that next year will be less - workdays are reorganized.
Even in the EU or in North America, parties are not united.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holiday, state holiday and holidays.
Holidays are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical ephemeris.
We celebrate the New Year too: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is a holiday - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven festivals written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and on October 23, the day to commemorate the revolution of 1956.
On August 20 we celebrate the founding of the State, on May 1st the feast of work, on November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased family and friends.
In addition, in our country are two-day festivals the Easter of Resurrection, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the holiday there is a single working day.
In exchange for the extended weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal rule is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory, however, for companies and service institutions that, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from December 24th practically stops life in the country, since according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
Next year several of our holidays will coincide with mid- or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in workdays than this year.
First, the agenda around the work party will be modified so that then, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in return Friday, May 2 is a holiday.
The other change is related to the October 23 party: on Saturday, October 18th, you will have to work instead of Friday, October 24th.
On the other hand, the coming year during the end of the year holiday will be able to rest, since from December 24 will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six Small Deterrents to Bitter Your Colleagues’ Lives
Emails that we forget to send, sound messages that we never receive, innocent lies that happen to us without realizing: all of them are part of our daily folklore at work.
You have to decide whether you adapt to small discomforts or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Advice.
Excuse me, I forgot to let you know that you’ve been searched from the marketing department,” says one of your colleagues.
That's why you didn't go on a date?
At best, feel it and try to fix the issue, maybe call the marketing department to tell them that they forgot to give you the message (this is the least common solution).
Most of the time the matter is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding with shameful explanations, it is worth meditating on the things with which you can embitter the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There’s nothing more irritating than when you want to grab a document, an office tool, or your phone and you can’t find them.
Do you remember that yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but for this morning it disappeared?
Do you find your lost pen on the table of one of your colleagues?
Don’t take anything away from your colleagues without asking them, because they will rightly be angry at you for stealing their stuff.
Do not take envelopes or post-it from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out ahead of time.
Do you gossip about your colleagues’ private lives?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what are you doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Do not pass on to everyone the information (speculations) you have about the private life of your colleagues!
Don’t abuse your colleague’s trust when he shares his innermost secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, even though others also know things about him.
Are you going on sick leave unjustifiably?
When you call the office and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or well, you feel that that day you prefer to rest; think that others should do your work, your impossible tasks, your work as a term.
Don't bother your colleague!
If you already know in advance that the next day you will not go to the office or something may happen to you, so you must stay at home, communicate them, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to face your absence the next day.
Tarareos, giggles, phone calls
Are you involved in your job, but you get the laughs of your colleagues out of it?
Have you involuntarily heard a phone conversation that would have been better not to listen to?
Don’t bother your colleagues with your bullshit, singing, loud conversations (except when you do them over their heads), kicking, constant blasphemies, expressing your discontents out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if they are not deepening at this time in a project (writing, planning, organization).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don’t blame others if you haven’t finished something in time, forgot to send an important letter or message!
Don’t mention the chaos that eventually reigns in the office, or the noise that your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that hurts others and you must repair the fault!
Ask how you can fix your fault!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and sneakers: very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Don’t wear comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Don’t be messed up, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday clothes, elegant and beautiful when your occupation demands it!
