Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which entered into force 1 November
In parallel to its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the vote by Congress on the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the government has submitted to public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim of having both come into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups agreed to highlight the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activity of the entities so that the markets function efficiently.
Mifid, which amends the Securities Markets Act, entails the modernisation of financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulation will allow the provision of financial advisory services to specialized firms as well as to natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (FSAs), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of transactions in financial instruments, so that regulated secondary markets are added to multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment firms to disclose in the market information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all transactions they perform, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In his passage through the Congressional Economics Committee, several modifications were incorporated, among which he points out that the securitized debts are considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high danger to the investor, which has been demonstrated by what happened with the U.S. high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can perform 30 years after the adoption in 1977 of the Royal Decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work for a third party, will not require the authorization of the CNMV and will be able to provide its services of marketing products and attracting customers to different investment companies at the same time.
