It's not the wooden boxes.
Whoever relates the terms Sweden and wooden box, thinks of Ikea, but does not think of Andy Warhol.
Or is it?
Currently the wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow weighing on Warhol’s list of works.
Most of the ninety-four Brilliant-Box "type" on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" put in doubt about the authenticity of Andy Warhol's Brillo-Boxes of the year 1968, the Museum Moderna Museet of Stockholm conducted internal investigations and came to disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former director of the museum Pontus Hultén also turned out to be the one hundred "in the Museum Moderna Museet's market, are false, and almost false.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created his first "Bright-Boxes" in New York, he painted the wooden boxes red, blue and white, with the same sample that they had "Bright" soap powder cartons.
According to Warhol, in the exhibition of his works in 1968 at the Museet Moderna were exhibited hundreds of Brillo-cardboard boxes. These did not Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the "Bright" cardboard factory.
These were not works of art, but specimens (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed to produce in Sweden a Brilliant wooden boxes, but they were not exhibited in the Modern Museet museum.
Witnesses of those times now speak of nearly fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Bright-Boxes" of "Stockhol type" authorized by Andy Warhol.
At auctions, some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden almost one hundred of the wooden boxes that Warhol left to him were produced and exposed.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hulten and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
By this time Warhol had already died for 3 years.
Lars Byström, the head of curators at the Museum Moderna Museet, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm.
On the contrary, the structure of the 1990 copies shows that the painting was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. It is also not about oil painting, but acrylic painting.
“These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and must be removed from Andy Warhol’s official Gloss-Box list,” says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet museum, adding that if the Andy Warhol Art Authentication Commission in New York will not come to any conclusion, the Moderna Museet museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/objects of exhibitions.
The Authentication Commission formally announced in July that it accepts these “serious allegations” that soap powder boxes are involved.
But from that moment everything remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers have surrendered who had entrenched themselves in a hotel in Manila and had demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Leader Antonio Trillanes, who blames the president for corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter he could not answer for spilling blood.
The soldiers loyal to the government had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been entrenched in the building for a few hours.
Nearly half of them, including Trillanes, were on trial on Thursday for attempting a 2003 coup that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, to suddenly be able to deposit with about 30 supporters.
Obviously the military policemen who were to watch him had passed into his ranks and followed his mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blockaded the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called for an urgent meeting of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the national security adviser, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
“People are fed up,” Trillanes said.
“We call on people to come into our ranks.”
General Danilo Lim, who previously led the elite Scout Reangers troop, said the other military troops wanted to follow suit shortly.
Major government critics on Thursday called for a major demonstration against the president.
His government has been criticized for corruption for months.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention because of the riot that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven attempts at coups against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
